First, you have bad data in the columns.  You should find that.  You can use:

    SELECT t.*
    FROM t
    WHRE TRY_CONVERT(date, t.datecol) IS NULL OR 
         TRY_CONVERT(time, t.timecol) IS NULL;

Note:  You might want to add a format for the `date` conversion, but if the default methods work (as they seem to in your case), that may not be necessary.

Once the data is fixed, or you decide you are happy with `NULL` values for the bad values, then you have two choices.

You can add computed columns:

    alter table t add real_date as (try_convert(date, t.datecol));
    alter table t add real_time as (try_convert(time, t.timecol));

Or, you can alter the columns in place:

    -- first convert to default string formats
    update t
        set datecol = try_convert(date, t.datecol),
            timecol  = try_convert(time, t.timecol);

    -- then alter the types
    alter t alter column datecol date;
    alter t alter column timecol time;

